JOHANNESBURG - The doctor treating triathlete Mhlengi Gwala says he doubts that he’ll return to competitive sport in the near future. This is after robbers attacked Gwala with a chainsaw on Wednesday morning, causing severe injuries to the athlete. READ: Crowdfunding campaign raises R300,000 for athlete attacked with chainsaw According to Dr O'Sharran Singh, the prospects of Gwala competing competitively anytime soon are not good. eNCA